As Frank Lampard volleyed in his first Manchester City goal against Chelsea on Sunday, the midfield veteran became the first player to score against 39 different Premier League clubs.

Unfortunately for Lampard, the last thing on his mind was celebrating such a feat as he all but apologised for scoring his side's equalising goal against his beloved Chelsea.

The 36-year-old has now overtaken former Manchester United striker Andy Cole, who held the record with goals against 38 different clubs.

