The former England midfielder has scored against 39 of the 46 teams that have played in the Premier League.

The majority of Lampard's goals came during his fruitful 13-year spell at Stamford Bridge, where he became Chelsea's all-time record scorer with 211  in all competitions.

The second-half strike was also his 172nd Premier League goal, putting Lampard just three goals away from joining Wayne Rooney and Thierry Henry as joint-third top scorers in Premier League history.

Lampard, who played 648 times for Chelsea, came on for David Silva after 78 minutes with City trailing 1-0 but seven minutes later he scored to make it 1-1, which was how the game ended. 

